{{About|ethnic Armenian organized crime in general, based mainly in Armenia and Russia|the [[Armenian-American]] criminal organization sometimes known as the "Armenian Mafia"|Armenian Power}} {{Infobox Criminal organization | name = Armenian mafia | founded = | founding location = [[Armenia]] | ethnicity = [[Armenian people|Armenian]] | membership = | territory = [[Armenia]], [[Russia]] and post-Soviet states, [[United States]] | criminal activities = [[Extortion]], [[racketeering]], [[assault]], [[murder]], [[political murder]], [[contract killing]], [[money laundering]], [[bribery]], [[embezzlement]], [[money laundering]], [[tax evasion]], [[political corruption]] | allies = [[Russian mafia]]{{cn|date=July 2016}} | rivals = [[Azerbaijani mafia]]{{cn|date=December 2016}}, [[Turkish mafia]]{{cn|date=December 2016}} }}
The '''Armenian mafia''' is a general term for organized criminal gangs based in [[Yerevan]], [[Moscow]]{{cn|date=December 2016}} and other major [[Russia]]n cities{{cn|date=December 2016}}, that consist of ethnic [[Armenians]]. It is spread over all [[post-Soviet states]]{{cn|date=December 2016}}. The structure is organized in clans called ''akhperutyuns'' (brotherhoods).<ref name=AN>[https://web.archive.org/web/20060709182218/http://www.armenianow.com/?action=viewArticle&AID=1390&lng=eng&IID=1071 "Mean Streets: A rare look at Armenia’s Capital clans"] - An ArmeniaNow Special Report by Vahan Ishkhanyan. March 3rd, 2006, [[ArmeniaNow]]. (Retrieved from the [[WebArchive]], July 9th 2006)</ref>
