{{Infobox language |name=Asilulu |altname= |states=[[Indonesia]] |region=[[Ambon Island]], [[Maluku Islands|Maluku]] |speakers=8,800 |date=1987 |ref = e18 |familycolor=Austronesian |fam2=[[Malayo-Polynesian languages|Malayo-Polynesian]] (MP) |fam3=[[Central–Eastern Malayo-Polynesian languages|Central–Eastern MP]] |fam4=[[Central Maluku languages|Central Maluku]] ? |fam5=[[East Central Maluku languages|East Central Maluku]] |fam6=[[Seram languages|Seram]] ? |fam7=[[Nunusaku languages|Nunusaku]] |fam8=[[Piru Bay languages|Piru Bay]] |fam9=West |fam10=Asilulu languages |iso3=asl |glotto=asil1242 |glottorefname=Asilulu }}
'''Asilulu''' is an [[Austronesian languages|Austronesian language]] of [[Ambon Island]] in the Moluccas, with some speakers on west [[Seram]]. It's a local trade language.
