There is a small community of '''ethnic Macedonians in the Czech Republic'''. Among the [[refugees of the Greek Civil War]] who were admitted to [[Czechoslovakia]] in the late 1940s, roughly 4,000 were of [[Macedonians (ethnic group)|Macedonian ethnicity]]; they [[refugee resettlement|resettled]] primarily in the Czech portion of the country.<ref>{{harvnb|Sloboda|2003}}</ref>

