{{Infobox language |name = Krahn |states = [[Liberia]], [[Ivory Coast]] |ethnicity=[[Krahn people|Krahn]] |speakers = {{sigfig|65400|2}} |date=1993–2006 |ref=e18 |familycolor = Niger-Congo |fam2 = [[Atlantic–Congo languages|Atlantic–Congo]] |fam3 = [[Kru languages|Kru]] |fam4 = [[Western Kru languages|Western Kru]] |fam5 = [[Wee languages|Wee]] |fam6 = Guere–Krahn |iso3=krw |glotto=west2488 |glottorefname=Western Krahn }}
'''Western Krahn''' is the principal language spoken by the [[Krahn people]] of [[Liberia]] and [[Ivory Coast]]. It is part of a series a dialects of the [[Wee languages|Wee]] (Guere) [[dialect continuum]] spoken by the Krahn and Guere peoples.
